<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Coming from a full spec MIND (44) Level 50 Sorcerer with more RvR experience then he cares to admit:<P>AoE mesmerize line: It can be quite useless in certain situations, especially large scale battles. This is because (1) Allied players can and will break the mez with weapons, or other mass AE spells, (2) Enemy player is currently immune, (3) Enemy player simply resists. This will spell death for the Sorcerer if he/she isn't already. We need an alternative.<P>AoE STR/CON debuff line: This was once a viable alternative to mez. If this spell is changed to very noticibly debuff the max health of the target(s), especially at full spec, it would be a useful alternative again.<P>CHARM line: Not very accessable in most situations, an idea would be to add high level casting pets in enemy frontiers and make them accessable, there are currently none. Add some meelee & casting pets that are more accessable, in Albion frontier. Also, definately let us HEAL our pet when it is not in combat. <P>In conclusion (anti-rant): We die all the time as-is from all types of enemy players. But a lone nightshade or ranger can get us every time. This is a lot more painful then "being mezzed for a minute". Thank you for your time.<P>Erebus Delirium<BR>realm rank 4.7<P>--------------------<P>ReincarnatedGod<P>"a chew toy of the demi-gods"
