<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I don't have too many problems with mind.  Here are a few changes I would like to see.<P>1) For those who spec'd full mind, they should be able to charm higher level mobs. If your mind spec + any items you have (divided by 2) raises your mind over your current level, you should be able to charm creatures up to that mind spec.  For example, at level 50 you have 50 in mind and +6 in items you should be able to charm level 53 (50 + (6 /2)).  This would give them a reason to spec full mind.<P>2) Change our mind debuff to affect intelligence/dexterity, not strength (move the strength/con to the Body spec where it belongs). (Another option would be a mana drain)<P>3) Make the debuffs we have now actually do something.<P>--------------------<P>Malachai Mindbender<BR>Enigmatic of Avalon - Guinivere<BR>Sanguis Societat<BR>http://www.farrout.net/sanguis/memberlist.asp?memberID=8
