<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
<B>Mind Base</B><P><B>Amnesia</B> <BR>   Needs to do more then just one interrupt with a 3 sec cast time. As it currently is there is not a real reason to use this except to give a tank/spell cast an extra 2 secs to cast. This is Not AE like bards have, its casting time is way to long to even be used, and it does no detarget the attkers from the enemy&#8217;s hate list.<P><B>Mez</B><BR>  The 1 min timer was put in yet power cost was not eleviated from resists due to this 1 min timer. There should be no power loss if casted on a person whom resists due to the 1 min timer. The spell (like all AE&#8217;s) works off the resists of the Targeted person. If that person resists the spell is considered DOA. If the spell is not resisted then everyone else in the area gets another chance to resist. Resist rates for this spell are currently way to high with the added 1 min timer right now.<P><B>Speed Buff</B><BR>  No change here from what I can see its working as intended.<P><B>Mind Spec</B> <P><B>Charm</B><BR> Sorcerer&#8217;s are &#8220;supposed&#8221; to be the Mind experts in Albion, the current set up of the class could not further set the class from that claim. All the spells a Sorcerer has in their Mind spec line someone else in the realm has it also and can use those spells a lot safer then a Sorcerer can. Our charms only allow for even con pets. We have no heal for these pets. We use 25% of our Exp to charm these pets. We have very few pets in PvE AND RvR. Lyonesse, Dartmoor, and I believe Cornwall are being looked at for more pets, yet this still does not fix the problems with certain levels not obtaining and utilizing an even con&#8217;d pet. At the very least a Sorcerer whom gives up their dmg spells and other utilities from the other spell lines for specing so high in Mind should get an added bonus (maybe new spell) that would allow a Sorcerer to charm a higher level con pet. Gives No RP&#8217;s.<P><B>Str/Con</B>  <BR>  With the changes to debuffs specializing in this spell line to get the highest debuff offers no benefits. With the changes debuffs total amounts where cut in half. If casted on a non buffed player their posted totals are cut in half again. While this &#8220;may&#8221; benefit if casting on a caster type this in no way benefits on casting these on a melee type. Casters are supposed to kill tanks from what we where told. This is untrue with these debuffs at their curret state. Unlike the Champions Sorcerers whom spec high enough to get the last level debuff are greatly gimping themselves now. Sorcerers whom spec to the highest Debuff are greatly reducing their dmg output because they cannot spec high enough in another spell line to get a decent DD spec&#8217;d spell. Yes we have lifetap but even that is to low while partnered with these debuffs to do any real dmg. Gives no RP.<P><B>AE Mez</B><BR>  The 1 min timer was put in yet power cost was not eleviated from resists due to this 1 min timer. There should be no power loss if casted on a person whom resists due to the 1 min timer. The spell (like all AE&#8217;s) works off the resists of the Targeted person. If that person resists the spell is considered DOA. If the spell is not resisted then everyone else in the area gets another chance to resist. Resist rates for this spell (and others) are currently way to high with the added 1 min timer right now. Add this to the bugs with Interrupts and casters in general are very close to useless in RvR. A caster who&#8217;s spells do not stick or cannot be casted do to interrupts is a dead caster. Where as a melee who gets a miss or failed style,bow shot, shout, etc&#8230; still has a chance to getaway. Gives no RP.<P><BR> Captain Crusader
</FONT>
