Lots of good ideas here, so to avoid repeating, I'll just say that the biggest issues (that haven't been said) that I see are: <P>agro management is very important and something we do very well in pve, but there is no way to manage agro in pvp. <P>Most of the mind spells either don't work or else they have a weakened effect in pvp, so the lessons we learned growing up no longer apply.<P>The two ideas are kind of tied together since the spells we use for agro management (amnesia, confusion, charm,...) don't really have an effect in pvp aside from interrupting. Those spells should be given an effect of making the target loose thier target, choose a new target, not be able to target, etc.<P>--Winin
